er than from remote or fictitious antiquity, the story compilers show how these virtues are not abstract or monolithic norms, but play out within the contingencies of time and space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aChinese fictionyMing dynasty, 1368-1644xHistory and criticism. 0aChinese fictionyQing dynasty, 1644-1912xHistory and criticism. 0aEthics in literature. 0aLiterature and moralszChinaxHistoryy17th century. 0aShort stories, ChinesexHistory and criticism. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846991140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438469911423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438469911/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles